## STACK & STRUCTURE

React 19 ¬∑ TypeScript ¬∑ Vite ¬∑ Tailwind CSS v4 ¬∑ shadcn/ui (Radix) ¬∑ Heroicons
24/outline (same family + native 1.5 stroke as the app; `lucide-react` was
removed, including the accordion chevron).

```
src/
  content/site.ts        ALL copy ‚Äî edit here, never in components
  index.css              every design token
  assets/                logo.svg + mark.svg (imported as modules, not /public)
  components/
    primitives.tsx       Frame / Section / Heading / Lede / Footnote
    icons.tsx            Heroicons map + Wordmark + Mark
    sections/            one file per section, composed in App.tsx
    ui/                  shadcn: accordion, button, input, label, textarea
  lib/utils.ts           cn() with extendTailwindMerge ‚Äî see gotchas
```

Sections in order: Hero ¬∑ Problem ¬∑ Difference ¬∑ Volume ¬∑ Cost ¬∑ How it works ¬∑
Features ¬∑ Who it's for ¬∑ FAQ ¬∑ Request access ¬∑ Footer.

Logo/mark are **imported as ES modules, not served from `/public`**, so the
bundler fingerprints them and no stray file can shadow the name. The favicon
is inlined as a data URI in `index.html` for the same reason. (This mattered:
something outside the session twice overwrote `public/` with another
project's assets.)

---

## THREE GOTCHAS THAT WILL BITE AGAIN

1. **tailwind-merge silently deletes the type scale.** The roles
   (`text-body`, `text-lead`, ‚Ä¶) are custom theme values, so twMerge reads
   them as *colour* utilities and drops them when a class string also holds
   `text-muted-foreground`. `src/lib/utils.ts` registers them via
   `extendTailwindMerge`. **Add any new role there too** or it will vanish at
   runtime with no error.

2. **Tailwind v4 has no `--duration-*` theme namespace.** `duration-fast`
   compiles to *nothing at all*, silently. Components must use
   `duration-[var(--duration-fast)]`.

3. **The focus ring must stay UNLAYERED.** shadcn ships `outline-none` as a
   utility; utilities live in a cascade layer, so the same rule inside
   `@layer base` loses and the ring disappears with no warning. The rule sits
   at the very bottom of `index.css`, outside any layer, with `!important`.

---

## DESIGN TOKENS (all in src/index.css)

- **Type roles:** `text-micro` 11 ¬∑ `caption` 12 ¬∑ `small` 13 ¬∑ `body` 15 ¬∑
  `h3` 17 ¬∑ `lead` 17‚Üí19 ¬∑ `h2` / `h2-lg` / `stat` / `display` fluid clamps.
  Nothing on the page uses an arbitrary `text-[‚Ä¶]` value.
- **Radius:** 10px controls/cards, 16px the one panel (matches the app).
- **Motion:** `--duration-fast` 120ms (hover/press) ¬∑ `--duration-base` 160ms
  (overlays/disclosure) ¬∑ `--duration-slow` 400ms (the one orchestrated
  mount), all on `cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1)`. No scroll-triggered reveals
  anywhere ‚Äî content is never gated on JS or motion.
- **Focus:** accent at 55%, 2px, 2px offset. Identical to the app.

---

## KNOWN ISSUE ‚Äî CTA CONTRAST (decide this)

Primary CTAs are white on `#35ABFF` = **2.49:1**. That fails WCAG AA (needs
4.5:1 for this text size; even the lenient 3:1 UI threshold misses). White-on-
accent-500 was chosen deliberately to match the app, which ships the same
pair. Three ways out, all keeping both brand hexes exact:

1. Darken the fill to `accent-700` `#1478C4`, label stays white ‚Üí **4.74:1**.
2. Keep `#35ABFF`, set the label in ink ‚Üí **7.6:1** (what it was before).
3. Accept it, consistent with the app.

The app has the same defect in `src/components/ui/primitives.tsx` (`primary`
variant) and is worth fixing there too.

